.el .ds Aq '
.TH daft-shared 1  "daft-shared 1.6.3" 
.SH NAME
daft\-shared \- Manage shared files across worktrees
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdaft\-shared\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Centralize untracked configuration files (.env, .idea/, .vscode/, etc.)
so they are shared across worktrees via symlinks.
.PP
Files are stored in .git/.daft/shared/ and symlinked into each worktree.
Use \*(Aqmaterialize\*(Aq to make a worktree\-local copy, and \*(Aqlink\*(Aq to rejoin
the shared version.
.PP
Without a subcommand, shows status.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
daft\-shared\-add(1)
Collect file/dir from current worktree into shared storage
.TP
daft\-shared\-remove(1)
Stop sharing a file (materialize everywhere, then remove)
.TP
daft\-shared\-materialize(1)
Replace symlink with a local copy in current worktree
.TP
daft\-shared\-link(1)
Replace local copy with symlink to shared version
.TP
daft\-shared\-status(1)
Show shared files and per\-worktree state
.TP
daft\-shared\-sync(1)
Ensure all worktrees have symlinks for declared shared files
.TP
daft\-shared\-manage(1)
Interactive TUI for managing shared file state across worktrees
.TP
daft\-shared\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v1.6.3
